description: {"blocks":[{"key":"dan67","text":"Protocol for the evaluation of pUb kinetics using 3D-SIM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"camjf","text":"Wash HeLa cells expressing doxycycline-inducible Parkin with 1x PBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8asob","text":"Add Trypsin to cells for 5 min and incubate at 37°C to dissociate cells from plastic well","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1scd0","text":"Resuspend cells in 1 mL DMEM media","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8b5p5","text":"Count cells","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"60nu9","text":"Seed appropriate number of cells onto 18x18mm Marienfeld Precision cover glasses thickness No. 1.5H (tol. ± 5 μm).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f2igh","text":"Top up glass bottom dish with either 1 mL DMEM and place cells back into incubator","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"758cu","text":"The next day exchange DMEM with DMEM + 2µg/ml doxycycline for 18h to induce Parkin expression.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4j2ts","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4tq7u","text":"Day 0: Treat AAVS1-TRE3G-NGN2 cells with Accutase and plate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated 6-well plates (2x105 cells/well) in ND1 Medium supplemented with Y27632 (10 μM).  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bg0cp","text":"ND1 Medium:  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fd4o","text":"DMEM/F12 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ig8l","text":"N2 (100x)        1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1agfe","text":"BDNF              10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7r7hg","text":"NT3                 10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8nhc","text":"NEAA (100X) 1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4smqo","text":"Laminin           0.2 μg/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9lu9d","text":"Doxycycline    2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9dmt9","text":"Day 1: Replace the medium with ND1 Medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3elij","text":"Day 2: Replace the medium with ND2 Medium.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fvai7","text":"ND2 Medium  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aeja6","text":"Neurobasal medium  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"26m72","text":"B27 (50x)                    1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3fp81","text":"GlutaMax (100x)         1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ehdsh","text":"BDNF                          10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1bhah","text":"NT3                             10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fu7pm","text":"Doxycycline                2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"an6t2","text":"Day 4: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b4s6c","text":"Day 6: Treat the cells with Accutase and replate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated  18x18mm Marienfeld Precision cover glasses thickness No. 1.5H (tol. ± 5 μm).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"98k8g","text":"Day 8 and thereafter: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well every other day.  ·       ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e6taa","text":"Doxycycline can be withdrawn on Day.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5du46","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cf02p","text":"Aspirate DMEM and fix cells in warm paraformaldehyde 3% Glutaraldehyde 0.35% in 0.1M Sodium Cacodylate, pH 7.4Aspirate PFA solution and wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"47o0n","text":"Permeabilize the cells by adding 0.2% Triton X-100 in PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9u7qo","text":"Remove the detergent solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4jo40","text":"Block cells for 10 min with 3% BSA – 1x PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"93ghe","text":"Remove BSA solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6irgu","text":"Incubate with primary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS over night at 4°C with gentle shaking.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aalei","text":"a.     Anti-HSP60 (mouse)  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bp68i","text":"b.     Anti-pUb (rabbit)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1m88k","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"74o6n","text":"Incubate with secondary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS for 45 min – 1h.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"anqh7","text":"a.     Goat anti-mouse AlexaFlour 488  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cd4m1","text":"b.     Goat anti-rabbit AlexaFluor 568","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"739q3","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a9mo3","text":"Add DAPI 1:2000 to wells for 5 min with gentle shaking.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ka9","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cibed","text":"Wash coverslips with 1x PBS and mount in Vectashield (Vector Laboratories, H-1000-10) on glass slides.Exchange PBST with 1x PBS and keep cells at 4°C until imaging. Image within the next few days. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"daujf","text":"Image cells on DeltaVision OMX v4 using an Olympus 60x / 1.42 Plan Apo oil objective (Olympus, Japan). Record 405, 488 and 568 channels using a front-illuminated sCMOS (PCO Photonics, USA) in 512x512px image size mode, 1x binning, 125 nm z-stepping and with 15 raw images taken per z-plane (5 phase-shifts, 3 angles).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6ovgg","text":"Reconstruct raw images using CUDA-accelerated 3D-SIM reconstruction code (https://github.com/scopetools/cudasirecon) based on Gustafsson et al. (2008[FK1] ). The Optimal optical transfer function (OTF) was determined via an in-house build software, developed by Talley Lambert from the NIC / CBMF (GitHub: https://github.com/tlambert03/otfsearch, all channels were registered to the 528nm output channel, Wiener filter: 0.002, background: 90).   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1kbd2","text":"Import composite .dv stacks into Imaris (v9.7) and convert into native .ims files.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"arlkm","text":"Import into Imaris Arena and perform global background subtraction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"947pn","text":"Segment pUb and mitochondrial objects from seeds (XY starting diameter: 0.08µm == pixel size of images), segmented based on automatic thresholding with local background subtraction and splitting of touching objects (0.4µm).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fg570","text":"Pipe segmented objects into Imaris Vantage module for further analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"enp6d","text":"In Vantage, compute nearest neighbour distances of pUb to pUb and between pUb and mitochondria, as well as volume of segmented objects.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9p3qm","text":"Test pipeline on WT control cells and then applied for batch processing on all other genotype to allow for unbiased segmentation and analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cra6h","text":"Plot results in your tool of choice for graphing and statistical analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Evaluation of pUb kinetics using 3D-SIM
